  "footnotes": [
    {
      "id": "1",
      "text": "Students with a score of 5 on the Economics AP exam may substitute 14.03 Microeconomic Theory and Public Policy."
    },
    {
      "id": "2",
      "text": "Or an approved alternative in statistics (consult department)."
    },
    {
      "id": "3",
      "text": "May be replaced by an additional elective subject in economics."
    },
    {
      "id": "4",
      "text": "This chart has been calculated based on an overlap of 36 units (three subjects) between the HASS General Institute Requirement and the departmental requirements. Students who develop a program of study with more overlap will be able to select more unrestricted electives to meet the number of total units beyond the GIRs required for an SB degree."
    }
